When we reach critical mass, there will be spontaneus self organisation... See how complex stuff is: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-organization#/media/File:Complex_systems_organizational_map.jpg You did a good job. See: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-organization

We are grateful to @sama99 for the idea, and @kevalin for being the nucleus. Hyperscale is a great idea and it is one of those things that in a span of 10 years will be a big hit. It will reshape the VC industry. For now, I think the hybrid model that is being done is the best safe and legal approach.

We're going to start making 2-5 investments per week. This number will increase as we go. I don't have time to lead everything. Right now the highest leverage thing that I can be focused on is investments. Can't build the entire ecosystem. Need someone else to focus on this!

Okay. I can understand.
Let me start with high readmap, why we need it and how we can develop it.
We can focus on the ecosystem dont worry

If you’re familiar with graph theory and directed acyclic graphs, you can use that when thinking about the roadmap and how to develop Sphere. 

On the surface Sphere is a directory that helps facilitate DAO <> Contributor coordination, but beneath the surface it should help Hyperscale draw a DAG of the ecosystem, to determine the strengths of the connections and the direction of the ecosystem. Tracking KPIs that convey the strength of a connection is crucial. Because then we know which DAOs are the biggest nodes in our graph, thus which new DAOs we should back to grow that node’s micro-ecosystem.
Right point. And these all data from Sphere will be going to help AI in training. So in the future, AI can make decisions based on those data and take calls on funding or helping that DAO.

@kir @pawel @BenJ @Satoshiba @mhrnik @Aswanth and the whole community

Proposal for a streamlining initiative

So I was thinking about how we could delegate stuff/work faster more efficiently. That way Kevalin could focus on investments and stuff, people would know exactly who to approach for what. No more delayed updates cos someone is overburdened.

There would be more flow of info, this no more doubt as to who signs off what stuff.  No more in the dark.

So we could use restructure a bit. Pardon me if this has already been done, I am unsure. 

I feel we need the following to be elected/nominated or self-nominated, I mean whoever can commit an hour or more time daily and is experienced could be a right fit.

Lead Developers 
- Backend: Pawel? mhrnik?
- Frontend: Kir?, BenJ?, Aswanth?

Lead Designer/Artist: Satoshiba? (Good art/design/experience/portfolio)

Chief Editor: ? (Prior experience/publication)

Chief Community Manager: jkey?

Project Manager: pawel? kir? BenJ?

Chief Legal: ?

Chief Marketing: ?

Product Manager: kevalin?

L3: All Respective folks could consult/work with the Leads / Chiefs.
L2: All Leads could consult/work with the Project Manager. 
    All Chiefs could consult/work with both Product and Project Managers.
L1: Project Manager could consult/work with Product Manager. See: https://www.productplan.com/learn/product-manager-vs-project-manager/
L1 + L2 + L3: Free flow of Information, Data, Text, Media, Code to and from all levels wherever needed.

We also need to have all tools listed and in a standard place known to everybody and easy to find by newcomers. We need to define what tools are used for what and location / URL and paste them here somewhere on Discord for easy discovery.

Development: Github - Hyperscale repos
Design/Art: Figma and Github - Hyperscale repos
Text and Media: Google Doc with copies in Git Hub, links in Discord
Project and Product Management: Trello, Discord
Community Management: Discord

Another request is the free flow of information and the courage to ask. If anybody finds an issue or something that feels unusual, they should be free and have the courage to ask/point it out in relevant threads here. Avoids guesswork, misunderstanding, and negative vibe that comes with doubts. Any problem is found, just ask policy - no shadow community (a hidden community within a community) / polarisation that way. If an impartial conflict resolution and explosives disposal is needed, I can be that person.

Thanks for putting the time in to this! 🙌🏻 

I think it's a strong proposal and we will be forced to adapt a structure like this at some point - so we may as well get on the front foot!

The key things for me are:
1. Tools, onboarding and project resources - everyone knows it's scattered at the moment, and it won't take much to clean this up. Just permission / consensus for members to go ahead.

2. Communication - there's a meme somewhere that says the toughest thing in being part of a DAO is working out what the hell is going on, and it's true! There's no such thing as over-communicating when things are fragmented like this in the early days. 

Personally, I have time (~2 days per week) that I can put towards Hyperscale, and I'd love to in any of the roles mentioned above.

I'd also advocate @AMICA as an adjudicator of sorts - you seem to have a good grip of what's going on!
